body:
We want to initially support the following crypto algorithms (the ones supported out-of-the-box by Go: https://golang.org/pkg/crypto/):

- MD4, MD5
- SHA1, SHA224, SHA256, SHA384, SHA512, SHA512_224, SHA512_256
- RIPEMD160


General outline proposal for Crypto API

1. Provide flexible API for each crypto algorithm as follows:

```js
import { crypto } from 'k6/crypto';

export default function() {
    let hasher = crypto.createHash("sha1");
    hasher.update("some data");
    let hash = hasher.digest("hex");
    console.log(hash);
}
```

2. Provide simple wrapper functions for common use:

```js
import { crypto } from 'k6/crypto';

export default function() {
    let hash = crypto.sha1("some text", "hex");
    console.log(hash);
}
```

