For the initial implementation of the Crypto module (https://github.com/loadimpact/k6/issues/19) we excluded HMAC. We want it now :)

General outline proposal for HMAC Crypto API

Provide flexible API as follows:
```js
import { crypto } from 'k6/crypto';

export default function() {
    let hmac = crypto.createHmac("sha256", "a secret");
    hmac.update("some data");
    let hash = hmac.digest("hex");
    console.log(hash);
}
```

Provide a simple wrapper function for common use:
```js
import { crypto } from 'k6/crypto';

export default function() {
    let hash = crypto.hmac("sha256", "a secret", "some text", "hex");
    console.log(hash);
}
```

The hashing algorithm ("sha256" in examples above) should be selectable from the available hashing algorithms, see: https://github.com/loadimpact/k6/blob/master/js/modules/k6/crypto/crypto.go#L106
